# March Machine Learning Mania 2026 — Results Walkthrough

## Objective
Beat the previous agent's best score of **0.14770** on the March Mania 2026 Kaggle competition (Brier Score, lower is better).

## Result

| Submission | Public LB | CV Brier | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| Shot 1 (baseline) | 0.14770 | 0.1485 | Elo + Seed logistic regression |
| **Killer** | **0.10343** 🎯 | 0.1386 | 9-model multi-seed ensemble |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **0.10343** is a **30% improvement** over the previous best of 0.14770.

## Killer Submission Architecture

### Features (26 total)
- **Elo** (MOV-adjusted): `elo_diff`, `elo1`, `elo2`
- **Seeds**: `seed_diff`, `seed1`, `seed2`
- **Efficiency metrics**: `off_rtg_diff`, `def_rtg_diff`, `net_rtg_diff`, `efg_diff`, `tov_diff`, `oreb_diff`, `ftrate_diff` (late-season 2x weighted)
- **Team quality**: `win_pct_diff`, `margin_diff`, `net_rtg1`, `net_rtg2`
- **Massey ordinals**: `massey_diff`, `massey1`, `massey2`
- **Strength of schedule**: `sos_diff`
- **Defensive metrics**: `blk_rate_diff`, `stl_rate_diff`, `ast_rate_diff`
- **Tournament experience**: `tourney_exp_diff`
- **Gender**: `gender`

### Model Ensemble
- 3 seeds × 3 model types = **9 models** averaged
- XGBoost (500 trees, depth 4, lr 0.03)
- LightGBM (500 trees, depth 4, lr 0.03)
- CatBoost (500 iters, depth 4, lr 0.03)

